	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_000993_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>57 Sloane St</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> April <add place="inline" hand="#hand01">[1857]</add></p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>Major Vardon</persName></p>
<lb/><p>Can you possibly 
<lb/>find the scientific 
<lb/>names of the Lake 
<lb/>shells brought 
<lb/>home by <persName>Oswell</persName><reg>.</reg>
<lb/>He is in town 
<lb/>now and called 
<lb/>here a day or two 
<lb/>ago. I was out<reg>.</reg>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_000993_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>I send you by this 
<lb/>post three pieces 
<lb/>of the book. I have 
<lb/>got <persName>Mr Binney</persName>
<lb/>to aid me too 
<lb/>in revision<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>Went yesterday 
<lb/>to the <persName>Lord Mayor</persName>
<lb/>&amp; got Â£200 - and 
<lb/>told him I wanted 
<lb/>the money put 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_000993_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>into the bank 
<lb/>of Coutts &amp; co. So 
<lb/>I hope <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Wire</persName>
<lb/>will save himself 
<lb/>the trouble of 
<lb/>finding it for me<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>Ever yours 
<lb/><persName>D Livingstone</persName></p>
			
